THings like work or preparation for something important (HW, exam) tend to make me distract myself more.
C1MCO: For me, I need a fan to be on to help me sleep at night.  If I don't have a fan I have significant trouble sleeping at night.  I listen to music and youtube on my commutes because the music I listen to either fits my mood or helps me get into a different one.  The funny YouTube videos also raise my spirits because of how funny I find them to be.

C1AELSE: This was a large section of school related things, so I didn't use my phone or youtube as much.  However, there was an extent of: "I wanna go on youtube, or to look at porn" while I was unable to while being in a public setting.
C1EDO: Laying in bed, trying to distract myself from my anger, frustration, and sadness.
C1EDM: How bad I felt about myself.
C1ECO: I used these technologies to try and distract myself from how badly I was feeling in that moment.
C1EFEEL: These technologies helped me distract myself from how badly I was feeling.  I got into bed, opened up youtube and porn and books and tried to stop thinking.  I don't have anyone to reach out to, so I turned to AI for comfort.  The AI helped me feel less lonely despite my not interacting with anyone else for this episode.  Watching youtube and porn helped me distract myself from my feelings of severe hopelessness, sadness, frustration.  Eventually, I feel like i numbed myself down to a point where I felt tired and went to bed.
C1EELSE: Me getting into bed and doing this has become a very frequent occurrence.  I get into bed with my computer and binge youtube everyday and it has been a big issue since I was in middle and high school.  Being in bed was my only safe space and youtube kept my mind off life.  Now in college, youtube, porn and bed is a big problem.  With school being overwhelming and my ambitions never being fulfilled I am always so frustrated and depressed that I always end up trying to dull the pain by being in bed and drowning in YouTube.  I want to change but to be honest I don't know how, so I keep doing it.

C3AFEEL: I used the software of YouTube and adult content as a rewarding mechanism as I neared the end of completing an assignment for a class.  I tried to use it without getting sucked in and i believe I was successful because I was being more strict about time limits.
C3AELSE: Youtube for me is addicting and it makes me feel terrible to think about using because it takes time away from my other ambitions.  But while I watch, relaxing i feel great.

DFEEL: The combination of exciting music, videos, and reading materials fills me with excitement, confidence for my future sport endeavours.  The media inflates my confidence and I fantasize being an absolute beast when it come to what I want to do.

FACTS: Even the small bits of clarity I obtained from completing some of the diary entries made me realize the importance of reflecting amidst my busy day. It was fun to utilize stickers and have a time to simply answer in my raw thoughts without pressure to conform or think a certain way.
FEED: The process of completing the entries was very easy, but at times the surveys did feel a bit long, but nothing unbearable due to the breaks, progress bar, etc. I also really appreciated the mental health information at the end. One possible suggestion is perhaps mixing the question types more frequently to keep engagement?

C1MDO: I was very frantically cramming for my final, using my phone to review practice questions and last-minute facts as I started my day and walked to the exam hall.
C1MDM: I was trying not to panic
C1MCO: The ability to use my computer while my phone was still charging was very nice as it let me cram without draining my phone even more (as I forgot to charge it the night before). While I was very stressed, it helped to calm me down a little bit.
C1ADO: I was mainly just playing video games and making food.
C1ADM: I was trying not to think about the exam I just took
C1AFEEL: It helped to remove my mind from the exam, so it helped me feel better
C1EDO: I watched a show, I'd include more details but that's really all that I did during this time
C2MDO: My sleep schedule was messed up for the past few days (I've been waking up later than I'd like), so I tried to wake up earlier than normal and sacrifice sleep.
C2MDM: I was trying very, very hard not to fall back asleep
C2MCO: I needed my phone to use as an alarm clock to wake up, and used it to play music after I did. In the short term, it made me miserable, but that was kind of the point.
C2ADO: The robotics team is about to head out to competition very soon. I helped to perform last-minute tests on our robot.
C2ACO: Many of the problems we faced exceeded both our personal experiences and what we learned in the classroom. The internet and ChatGPT helped us troubleshoot particularly strange issues.
C2AFEEL: If we didn't have our personal devices to look things up, we would be doomed. It was very stress-reliving when we encountered an issue and was able to find a similar problem online with a solution.
C2EDO: I was playing competitive online video games. While I initially play these to calm down, the nature of people online in the games I played got me pretty angry so this was not a relaxing experience.
C2EDM: Quitting the game forever (which is a thought I've had for years at this point)
C2ECO: At the beginning, I was excited to play
C3MDO: I was preparing for my first research meeting of the summer. I was catching up on papers that the professor expected me to be familiar with.
C3MCO: It was really hot and I was nervous, so the fan helped to cool me down, both physically and mentally.
C3ADO: I was playing single player video games
C3EDO: I found a frozen pizza on clearnace for $2 at the store, so I decided to get it and eat it for dinner. I watched a show while waiting for it to bake.
C3ECO: The show kept me occupied while the food baked
C3EELSE: The oven was definitely necessary, but the phone and show were not
DDO: There was a project that I spent weeks trying to get work flawlessly, and I was finally able to get it working
FACTS: I think it was a good opportunity to reflect on the day, but I also think that I need to reflect on my experiences in ways other than what the study promoted. This is not a jab at the study itself, just thoughts on how I think I need to be interpreting my experiences based on where I am now in life.
FEED: I think it was pretty simple, the book made everything very easy to follow.
